                                     242 *STATUS                                                                 00162021
                                     243 *                                                                       00168021
                                     244 *   CHANGE LEVEL 000                                                    00174021
                                     245 *                                                                       00180021
                                     246 *FUNCTION/OPERATION                                                     00186021
                                     247 *                                                                       00192021
                                     248 *   CHECK SYNTAX OF DATA DIVISION ENTRIES, COMPUTES THE ATTRIBUTES      00198021
                                     249 *   ADDRESSING PARAMETERS OF THESE ENTRIES, AND STORES THEM IN A        00204021
                                     250 *   DICTIONARY WHERE THEY CAN BE REFERRED TO BY THE LATER PHASES WH     00210021
                                     251 *   DEAL WITH THE PROCEDURE DIVISION. PHASE 2 ALSO FORMATS THE DATA     00216021
                                     252 *   CONTROL BLOCKS (DCB), DATA EVENT CONTROL BLOCKS (DECB), AND BUF     00222021
                                     253 *   FOR FILES  SPECIFIED IN THE FILE SECTION.                           00228021
                                     254 *                                                                       00234021
                                     255 *                                                                       00240021
                                     256 *   THE FUNCTION/OPERATION AND GENERAL CONSIDERATION OF THE ACCESS      00246021
                                     257 *   ARE DESCRIBED IN DETAIL IN PLM AND PHASE 1 LISTING.                 00252021
                                     258 *                                                                       00258021
                                     259 *ENTRY POINTS                                                           00264021
                                     260 *                                                                       00270021

                                     526+*    HOUSEKEEPING FOR THE DICOT TABLE, NEEDED BY TAMER                  12240020
                                     527+*    THE DICOT TABLE IS THE TABLE USED TO HOLD INFORMATION ON THE       12330020
                                     528+*    DICTIONARY SEGMENTS.  IT CONTAINS AN ENTRY FOR EACH SECTION AND    12420020
                                     529+*    ITS ORDER CORRESPONDS TO THE ORDER OF THE SECTIONS.                12510020
                                     530+*      EACH ENTRY IS 12 BYTES LONG---                                   12600020
                                     531+*            BYTE  0   = CODE TESTED FOR STATUS OF SECTION.             12690020
                                     532+*            BYTES 1-3 = ADDRESS OF A DICT. SECTION IN CORE.            12780020
                                     533+*            BYTES 4-11= ADDRESS, ON DISK, OF A SPILLED SECTION.        12870020
                                     534+*                                                                       12960020
                                     535+*      THE CORE ADDRESS OF A SPILLED SECTION IS OBSOLETE UNTIL THE      13050020
                                     536+*      SECTION IS READ BACK IN FOR UPDATING.  THEN BOTH ADDRESSES, DISK 13140020
                                     537+*      AND CORE, ARE TRUE.  AFTER SPILL, UNTIL UPDATE, THE TRUE         13230020
                                     538+*      ADDRESS IS THAT IN BYTES 4-11 OF THE DICOT ENTRY FOR THE SECT.   13320020

                                     797+*     HASHES BCD NAME, LOCATES CORRES. HASH TABLE ENTRY                 36630020
                                     798+*    INPUT  R9=A(BCD NAME)       'ENT'  R9  'L' R9                      36720020
                                     799+*           R11= BCD NAME CNT            R11     R11                    36810020

                                     801+*           R10= A(HASH TABLE ENTRY)     R10     R10                    36990020
                                     802+*           R8/R9  EVEN/ODD  DIVIDEND                                   37080020
                                     803+*           R10/R11  EVEN/ODD  INCREM./COMPAR.                          37170020
                                     804+*                                                                       37260020
                                     805+*    HASHING FUNCTION                                                   37350020
                                     806+*      SEGMENT NAME (INCL. CNT) INTO 4 BYTE LENGTHS, ADD LENGTHS        37440020
                                     807+*      TOGETHER LOGICALLY, DIVIDE SUM BY SIZE OF HASH TABLE, MULT       37530020
                                     808+*      REMAIN. BY 3 TO OBTAIN DISPL. ADD IT TO A(HASH TABLE) AND        37620020
                                     809+*      PICK UP CORRES. ENTRY                                            37710020

                                    1935 *LDTEXT(GETNXT)  GETS LD-TEXT FROM BUFFER AND DISTRIBUTES IT TO WOR     04500021
                                    1936 *AREAS TO BE PROCESSED AT A LATER TIME. PICTURES ARE CONVERTED FROM     04506021
                                    1937 *SOURCE LANGUAGE TO INTERNAL LANGUAGE SO THAT THEY MAY BE PROCESSED     04512021
                                    1938 *BY THEIR RESPECTIVE PICTURE ANALYSIS ROUTINES. THE SUBSCRIPTING        04518021
                                    1939 *REQUIREMENTS ARE DETERMINED IN LDTEXT BY A CALL TO BMBSRN.             04524021
                                    1940 *TITLE 'LDTEXT'   -LEVEL DESCRIPTION TEXT PROCESSOR                     04530021
                                    1941 *STATUS                                                                 04536021
                                    1942 *FUNCTION/OPERATION- PHASE 2 RECEIVES ALL 01-49,77,88 ITEMS IN LD-T     04542021
                                    1943 *   THIS ROUTINE DETERMINES THE ATTRIBUTES OF THE ITEM AS FOLLOWS.      04548021
                                    1944 *   A.-GETNXT-TAKES THE LD-TEXT AND DISTRIBUTES IT INTO WORK AREAS.     04554021
                                    1945 *     THERE IS A PICTURE IN THE ITEM  -GSPICT- IS CALLED TO CHECK A     04560021
                                    1946 *     ENCODE IT. THE ROUTINE -BMBSRN- IS CALLED FOR ALL ITEMS TO        04566021
                                    1947 *     DETERMINE  THE SUBSCRIPTING REQUIREMENTS FOR THE ITEM             04572021
                                    1948 *   B.-COPYRN-IF 01 LEVEL HAS A COPY CLAUSE, ITS DATA-NAME IS SAVED     04578021
                                    1949 *     AND REPLACES THE DATA-NAME OF THE NEXT 01 LEVEL ITEM.             04584021
                                    1950 *   C.-BUSAGE-CHECKS THE USAGE CLAUSE COMPATIBILITY. IF A GROUP ITE     04590021
                                    1951 *     HAS A USAGE CLAUSE, ITS SUBORDINATE ITEMS MUST HAVE SAME USAG     04596021
                                    1952 *     APPROPRIATE PICTURE ANALYSIS RTN. IF ANALYSIS RTN. RETURNS WI     04602021
                                    1953 *     AN ERROR CODE, THE PICTURE IS CHANGED TO '9'.                     04608021
                                    1954 *     THE ITEM.                                                         04614021
                                    1955 *ENTRY POINT- -LDTEXT-   BAL  R14,LDTEXT                                04620021
                                    1956 *INPUT-      REG 7  POINTS TO  LD-TEXT IN BUFFER  (FILE 3 BUFFER)       04626021
                                    1957 *OUTPUT-     PARTIALLY BUILT DICTIONARY ENTRY                           04632021
                                    1958 *EXTERNAL ROUTINES                                                      04638021
                                    1959 *   -BMBSRN-  SUBSCRIPTING REQUIREMENTS                                 04644021
                                    1960 *   -GSPICT-  TRANSLATE SOURCE PICTURE TO CODE                          04650021
                                    1961 *EXITS- 1 NORMAL EXIT AT END OF PROCESSING                              04656021

0                                   2907 *BMBSRN DETERMINES THE SUBSCRIPTING REQUIREMENTS FOR AN ITEM. THE       10332021
                                    2908 *    NUMBER OF SUBSCRIPTS REQUIRED IS STORED IN THE MBS FIELD OF TH     10338021
                                    2909 *    ATTRIBUTES. THE DICTIONARY POINTER OF THE PRECEDING ITEM (OF T     10344021
                                    2910 *    NEXT HIGHEST SUBSCRIPTING LEVEL) IS PLACED IN THE ATTRIBUTE FI     10350021
                                    2911 *    OF THE CURRENT ITEM. ONLY 3 LEVELS OF SUBSCRIPTING ARE ALLOWED     10356021
                                    2912 *    AND LEVELS 01 WITH OCCURS CLAUSES HAVE THEIR OCCURS CLAUSES        10362021
                                    2913 *    DELETED. THE FOLLOWING ITEMS WOULD BE ACTED UPON AS FOLLOWS        10368021
                                    2914 *                            *MBS *DICTIONARY PTR TO ITEM *REMARKS      10374021
                                    2915 *    01 A                    *  0 *      NO POINTER FIELD *             10380021
                                    2916 *     02 B OCCURS 7          *  1 *      NO POINTER FIELD *             10386021
                                    2917 *      03 C OCCURS 6         *  2 *      POINTER TO ITEM B*             10392021
                                    2918 *      03 D                  *  1 *      POINTER TO ITEM B*             10398021
                                    2919 *       04 E OCCURS 7        *  2 *      POINTER TO ITEM B*             10404021
                                    2920 *       04 F                 *  1 *      POINTER TO ITEM B*             10410021
                                    2921 *        05 G OCCURS 8       *  2 *      POINTER TO ITEM B*             10416021
                                    2922 *     02 H OCCURS 9          *  1 *      POINTER IS ZERO  *             10422021
                                    2923 *     02 I                   *  0 *      NO POINTER FIELD *             10428021
                                    2924 *     02 J OCCURS 10         *  1 *      NO POINTER FIELD *             10434021
                                    2925 *      03 K OCCURS 6         *  2 *      POINTER TO ITEM J*             10440021
                                    2926 *       04 L OCCURS 7        *  3 *      POINTER TO ITEM K*             10446021
                                    2927 *       04 M OCCURS 8        *  3 *      POINTER TO ITEM K*             10452021
                                    2928 *        05 N OCCURS 9       *  3 *      POINTER TO ITEM M*THE OCCU     10458021
                                    2929 *        05 O                *  3 *      POINTER TO ITEM M* CLAUSE      10464021

-  LOC  OBJECT CODE    ADDR1 ADDR2  STMT   SOURCE STATEMENT                                       ASM 0201 11.03 02/14/15
0                                   3417 *=2      SOURCE PICTURE ANALYSIS-GSPICT                                 13392021
                                    3418 *GSPICT-SOURCE PICTURE ROUTINE                                          13398021
                                    3419 * GSPICT SCANS THE SOURCE PICTURE CHECKING FOR VALID PICTURE CHARAC     13404021
                                    3420 * AND DETERMINES THE PICTURE TYPE IF ALL THE CHARACTERS ARE VALID.      13410021
                                    3421 * VALIDATION IS DONE BY A TRANSLATE TABLE OF THE 256 BIT CONFIGURAT     13416021
                                    3422 * OF EBCDIC CONVENTION. EACH CHARACTER OF THE SOURCE PICTURE IS TRA     13422021
                                    3423 * LATED TO A CODE AND THIS CODE IS OR'ED INTO A CHECK BYTE(BVPCHK).     13428021
                                    3424 * ILLEGAL CHARACTERS HAVE X'FF' CODE IN THE TRANSLATE TABLE. THE VA     13434021
                                    3425 * OF THE CHECK BYTE DETERMINES THE PICTURE TYPE(PCTYPE). THE SOURCE     13440021
                                    3426 * PICTURE IS DISTRIBUTED TO IPT-INITIAL PICTURE TABLE AND IPLT-INIT     13446021
                                    3427 * PICTURE LENGTH TABLE. PARENTHESIS ARE DROPPED AND THEIR ENCLOSED      13452021
                                    3428 * LENGTHS ARE TRANSLATED TO BINARY BEFORE DISTRIBUTION TO IPT AND I     13458021
                                    3429 *                                                                       13464021
                                    3430 *                                                                       13470021
                                    3431 * THE CALLING SEQUENCE FOR GSPICT IS                                    13476021
                                    3432 *        ST    R15,RSAVE+60                                             13482021
                                    3433 *        L     R15,AGSDIC          AGSPIC IS ADCON FOR GSPICT           13488021
                                    3434 *        BALR  R14,R15                                                  13494021
                                    3435 *        L     R15,RSAVE+60                                             13500021

0                                   5429 *=2      ALPHABETIC AND ALPHANUMERIC PICTURE ROUTINE                    25464021
                                    5430 *                                                                       25470021
                                    5431 *BALPHA-ALPHABETIC-ALPHANUMERIC PICTURE ANALYSIS ROUTINE                25476021
                                    5432 *BALPHA CHECKS THE COMPATIBILITY OF USAGE AND LENGTH FOR ALDHABETIC     25482021
                                    5433 * AND ALPHANUMERIC PICTURE ITEMS. USAGE MUST BE DISPLAY, IF IT IS N     25488021
                                    5434 * THE PICTURE IS DROPPED AND REPLACED BY A PICTURE 9 BY ITEMAN(ITEM     25494021
                                    5435 * ANALYSIS ROUTINE). THE LENGTH MUST NOT BE GREATER THAN 32K BYTES,     25500021
                                    5436 * IT IS THE LENGTH IS TRUNCATED TO 32K. THE LENGTH IS STORED IN THE     25506021
                                    5437 * ATTRIBUTES FIELD.                                                     25512021
                                    5438 * BALPHA IS CALLED BY PICTAN WHEN PCTYPE BYTE HAS ALPHABETIC OR         25518021
                                    5439 * ALPHANUMERIC CODE. THE CODE IS                                        25524021
                                    5440 *                                                                       25530021
                                    5441 *        IC    R4,PCTYPE      INSERT PICTURE TYPE CODE IN REG 4         25536021
                                    5442 *        SLA   R4,2           MULTIPLY BY 4 FOR FULL WORD BNDRY         25542021
                                    5443 *        LA    R8,BPICTB      LOAD PICTURE TABLE ADDRESS IN REG 8       25548021
                                    5444 *        AR    R8,R4          ADD INDEX(R4) TO ADDRESS OF BPICTB TA     25554021
                                    5445 *        ST    R15,RSAVE+60   SAVE REG 15                               25560021
                                    5446 *        L     R15,0(0,R8)    PUT TABLE ADDRESS IN REG 15               25566021
                                    5447 *        BALR  R14,R15        CALL PROPER PICTURE ANALYSIS RTN          25572021
                                    5448 *        LTR   R14,R15        IF CALLED ROUTINE DELETES CURRENT ITE     25578021
                                    5449 *        L     R15,RSAVE+60    PICTURE, R15 WILL BE SET TO ZERO AND     25584021
                                    5450 *        BC    ZERO,BFIXPC     BRANCH WILL BE TAKEN TO BFIXDC, OTHE     25590021
                                    5451 *        BC    UNCOND, ELCOM  GO TO ELEM ITEM COMPATIBILITY RTN         25596021
                                    5452 *                                                                       25602021
                                    5453 *BPICTB IS A TABLE OF PICTURE ANALYSIS RTNS                             25608021
                                    5454 *BFIXPC INSERTS A PICTURE 9.                                            25614021
                                    5455 *THE MAIN ROUTINE PLACES THE PROPER MINOR CODE IN REG 3                 25620021
                                    5456 *                    0010 FOR ALPHABETIC ITEMS                          25626021
                                    5457 *                    0011 FOR ALPHANUMERIC ITENS                        25632021
                                    5458 *SO THAT THE EXECUTE INSTRUCTION BEXMIN CAN PLACE THE MINOR CODE        25638021
                                    5459 *IN THE ATTRIBUTE FIELD                                                 25644021
                             03B66  5460        USING *,R15                                                      25650021

0                                   5507 *=2      NUMERIC PICTURE PICTURE ANALYSIS-BNUMER                        25932021
                                    5508 *BNUMER--NUMERIC PICTURE ANALYSIS                                       25938021
                                    5509 *BNUMER CHECKS THE VALIDITY OF THE NUMERIC PICTURE WITH RESPECT TO      25944021
                                    5510 * CHARACTER CONFIGURATION, LENGTH, SCALE AND USAGE. THE NUMERIC LEN     25950021
                                    5511 *AND SCALE  ARE STORED IN THE ATTRIBUTES FOR THE ITEM. THERE ARE 3      25956021
                                    5512 * VALID USAGES FOR A NUMERIC ITEM.                                      25962021
                                    5513 *              DISPLAY          -EXTERNAL DECIMAL                       25968021
                                    5514 *              COMPUTATIONAL    -BINARY                                 25974021
                                    5515 *              COMPUTATIONAL-3  -INTERNAL DECIMAL                       25980021
                                    5516 * IF DISPLAY THE MACHINE LENGTH EQUALS THE NUMERIC LENGTH.              25986021
                                    5517 * IF COMPUTATIONAL THE MACHINE LENGTH IS SPECIFIED BY FOLLOWING TAB     25992021
                                    5518 *                                                                       25998021
                                    5519 *                 NUMERIC LGN * MACHINE LGN                             26004021
                                    5520 *                 *************************                             26010021
                                    5521 *                     1-4     *     2                                   26016021
                                    5522 *                     5-9     *     4                                   26022021
                                    5523 *                    10-18    *     8                                   26028021
                                    5524 *                                                                       26034021
                                    5525 *IF COMPUTATIONAL-3 THE MACHINE LENGTH =(NUMERIC LGN/2)+1.              26040021
                                    5526 *IF USAGE IS NOT ONE OF THESE THE PICTURE IS DROPPED.                   26046021
                                    5527 *MAXIMUM NUMERIC LGN IS 18.                                             26052021
                                    5528 *                                                                       26058021
                                    5529 *                                                                       26064021
                                    5530 *BNUMER IS CALLED BY PICTAN WHEN PCTYPE IS NUMERIC.                     26070021
                                    5531 *THE CALLING ROUTINE IS                                                 26076021
                                    5532 *                                                                       26082021
                                    5533 *                                                                       26088021
                                    5534 *        IC    R4,PCTYPE      INSERT PICTURE TYPE CODE IN REG 4         26094021
                                    5535 *        SLA   R4,2           MULTIPLY BY 4 FOR FULL WORD BNDRY         26100021
                                    5536 *        LA    R8,BPICTB      LOAD PICTURE TABLE ADDRESS IN REG 8       26106021
                                    5537 *        AR    R8,R4          ADD INDEX(R4) TO ADDRESS OF BPICTB TA     26112021
                                    5538 *        ST    R15,RSAVE+60   SAVE REG 15                               26118021
                                    5539 *        L     R15,0(0,R8)    PUT TABLE ADDRESS INTO REG 15             26124021
                                    5540 *        BALR  R14,R15        CALL PROPER PICTURE ANALYSIS RTN          26130021
                                    5541 *        LTR   R14,R15        IF CALLED ROUTINE DELETES CURRENT ITE     26136021
                                    5542 *        L     R15,RSAVE+60    PICTURE, R15 WILL BE SET TO ZERO AND     26142021
                                    5543 *        BC    ZERO,BFIXPC     BRANCH WILL BE TAKEN TO BFIXPC, OTHE     26148021
                                    5544 *        BC    UNCOND,BELCOM  GO TO ELEM ITEM COMPATIBILITY RTN         26154021
                                    5545 *                                                                       26160021
                                    5546 *BPICTB IS A TABLE OF PICTURE ANALYSIS RTNS                             26166021
                                    5547 *BFIXPC INSERTS A PICTURE 9.                                            26172021
                                    5548 *                                                                       26178021
                                    5549 *                                                                       26184021
                                    5550 *                                                                       26190021
                             03BFE  5551          USING *,R15                                                    26196021

0                                   5738 *=2      FLOATING POINT PICTURE ANALYSIS-BFLTPT                         27318021
                                    5739 *BFLTPT--FLOATING POINT PICTURE ANALYSIS                                27324021
                                    5740 *BFLTPT ANALYZES AN EXTERNAL FLOATING POINT PICTURE CHECKING CHARAC     27330021
                                    5741 * CONFIGURATION, LENGTH OF MANTISSA AND EXPONENT, AND USAGE. THE US     27336021
                                    5742 * MUST BE DISPLAY, IF IT IS NOT, THE PICTURE IS DROPPED AND AN ERRO     27342021
                                    5743 * CODE(REGISTER 15= 0) IS RETURNED TO PICTAN.                           27348021
                                    5744 *BFLTPT IS CALLED BY PICTAN WHEN PCTYPE  IS EXT. FLOAT. PT, BY THE      27354021
                                    5745 * FOLLOWING CODE.                                                       27360021
                                    5746 *                                                                       27366021
                                    5747 *                                                                       27372021
                                    5748 *        IC    R4,PCTYPE      INSERT PICTURE TYPE CODE IN REG 4         27378021
                                    5749 *        SLA   R4,2           MULTIPLY BY 4 FOR FULL WORD BNDRY         27384021
                                    5750 *        LA    R8,BPICTB      LOAD PICTURE TABLE ADDRESS IN REG 8       27390021
                                    5751 *        AR    R8,R4          ADD INDEX(R4) TO ADDRESS OF BPICTB TA     27396021
                                    5752 *        ST    R15,RSAVE+60   SAVE REG 15                               27402021
                                    5753 *        L     R15,0(0,R8)    PUT TABLE ADD.INTO R15                    27408021
                                    5754 *        BALR  R14,R15        CALL PROPER PICTURE ANALYSIS RTN          27414021
                                    5755 *        LTR   R14,R15        IF CALLED ROUTINE DELETES CURRENT ITE     27420021
                                    5756 *        L     R15,RSAVE+60    PICTURE, R15 WILL BE SET TO ZERO AND     27426021
                                    5757 *        BC    ZERO,BFIXPC     BRANCH WILL BE TAKEN TO BFIXPC, OTHE     27432021
                                    5758 *        BC    UNCOND,BELCOM  GO TO ELEM ITEM COMPATIBILITY RTN         27438021
                                    5759 *                                                                       27444021

0                                   6092 *=2      REPORT PICTURE ANALYSIS-BREPOR                                 29442021
                                    6093 *BREPOR--REPORT PICTURE ANALYSIS                                        29448021
                                    6094 *BREPOR ANALYZES A REPORT PICTURE CHECKING FOR LEGAL CHARACTER          29454021
                                    6095 * CONFIGURATION, TOTAL LENGTH, NUMERIC LENGTH, SCALE, USAGE, AND        29460021
                                    6096 * ASSOCIATED CLAUSES. THE TOTAL LENGTH CANNOT EXCEED 127 CHARACTERS     29466021
                                    6097 * IT DOES THE PICTURE IS CHANGED TO 9. IF THE NUMERIC LENGTH IS GRE     29472021
                                    6098 *THAN 18 THE PICTURE IS CHANGED TO 9. THE                               29478021
                                    6099 * USAGE MUST BE DISPLAY, IF IT SI NOT THE PICTURE IS DROPPED. IF TH     29484021
                                    6100 * NUMERIC CHARACTERS ARE ALL +, -, $, OR Z THE BLANK WHEN ZERO CLAU     29490021
                                    6101 * IS ASSUMED PRESENT AND THE BWZ BIT IN THE ATTRIBUTES IS SET TO 1.     29496021
                                    6102 * THE NUMERIC CHARACTERS ARE ALL *, THE *WZ BIT IS SET TO ONE. IF T     29502021
                                    6103 * BWZ CLAUSE IS GIVEN FOR THE LATTER CASE IT IS DELETED.                29508021
                                    6104 *  BREPOR IS CALLED BY PICTAN WHEN PCTYPE IS REPORT BY THE FOLLOWIN     29514021
                                    6105 *  CALLING ROUTINE                                                      29520021
                                    6106 *                                                                       29526021
                                    6107 *                                                                       29532021
                                    6108 *        IC    R4,PCTYPE      INSERT PICTURE TYPE CODE IN REG 4         29538021
                                    6109 *        SLA   R4,2           MULTIPLY BY 4 FOR FULL WORD BNDRY         29544021
                                    6110 *        AR    R8,R4          ADD INDEX(R4) TO ADDRESS OF BPICTB TA     29550021
                                    6111 *        ST    R15,RSAVE+60   SAVE REG 15                               29556021
                                    6112 *        L     R15,0(0,R8)    PUT TABLE ADDRESS INTO REG 15             29562021
                                    6113 *        BALR  R14,R15        CALL PROPER PICTURE ANALYSIS RTN          29568021
                                    6114 *        LTR   R14,R15        IF CALLED ROUTINE DELETES CURRENT ITE     29574021
                                    6115 *        L     R15,RSAVE+60    PICTURE, R15 WILL BE SET TO ZERO AND     29580021
                                    6116 *        BC    ZERO,BFIXPC     BRANCH WILL BE TAKEN TO BFIXPC, OTHE     29586021
                                    6117 *        BC    UNCOND,BELCOM  GO TO ELEM ITEM COMPATIBILITY RTN         29592021
                                    6118 *                                                                       29598021
                                    6119 *BPICTB IS A TABLE OF PICTURE ANALYSIS RTNS                             29604021
                                    6120 *BFIXPC INSERTS A PICTURE 9.                                            29610021
                                    6121 *                                                                       29616021
                                    6122 *                                                                       29622021
                                    6123 *                                                                       29628021

                                   14496 *                                                                       79866021
                                   14497 *        IT IS NOW MODIFIED SO THAT ALL RECORDS UNDER AN FD             79872021

                                   14504 *        ENTRY IN THE ORIGINAL QFILE TABLE, A NEW GN NUMBER             79914021
